  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "I want to run a new geth based on the disk snapshot of the whole home directory of the previously running full-archive node.\r\n\r\nIn geth's home directory there is other stuff than `chaindata/` dir. I understand `nodekey` file should be deleted, so geth autogenerate a new one in order not to confuse p2p network that the node already exist in the network.\r\n\r\nBut what about other files/folders, do I need to delete some of those as well to speed up booting new geth?\r\n",
