    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Use `geth <args> removedb`, this is a command for exactly that, so people don't have to delete files themselves. \r\nThe `<args>` is used if you have the datadir at a non-default location, so for example you could do `geth --datadir /foo/bar/bazonk removedb` \r\n\r\nThe command will ask you if it should delete \r\n1. The state database. Select yes\r\n2. The ancient database. This is the block bodies, receipts, headers etc. You can leave them intact, and not have to download ~400G from the network. \r\n3. The LES database .You can select yes to delete that. ",
